  <paragraphs>
    <title>Course Description</title>
    <p>
      An opportunity for supervised practicum field experience in mental health counseling. Guided by a cooperating Agency and University faculty, students participate in aspects of the counseling process which may include assessment, diagnosis and treatment, ethical considerations, and use of self in the counseling process. Connections between this practicum, the counseling internship, and the counseling field are discussed.  
    </p>
  </paragraphs>
  <paragraphs>
    <title>Prerequisites</title>
    <p>
      CPSY 901 Theories of Psychotherapy and Counseling, CPSY 911 Orientation to Counseling Practice, CPSY 921 Professional Issues in Counseling and Mental Health, CPSY 925 Psychopathology, and permission of the Program Coordinator. 
    </p>
  </paragraphs>
  <paragraphs>
    <title>Required Text and Subscriptions</title>
    <p>
      <pubtitle>Clinical Interviewing 7th edition</pubtitle>
      by Sommers-Flanagan, J., and Sommers-Flanagan, R. ISBN-10 1119981980. 
      PDF of full text will be posted in Canvas course for download. 
      You WILL need to purchase a monthly subscription for Time2Track to track your practicum hours. Please note FSU does not offer a paid student subscription for this resource. Visit this website to purchase subscription and see Appendix A of this syllabus for further details https://time2track.com/.
    </p>
  </paragraphs>
  <paragraphs>
    <title>Definitions of terms in Syllabus and Graduate Catalog </title>
    <p>
      <term>Counseling Practicum Student:</term>
      Is a graduate student in mental health counseling who is completing their professional preparation for the Master of Arts with a concentration in Mental Health Counseling.
    </p>
    <p>
      <term>Practicum Site Supervisor:</term>
      The counseling supervisor at the practicum site who meets Massachusetts state license guidelines. The primary responsibility of the site supervisor is to direct/supervise the day-to-day experiences of the practicum student. 
    </p>
    <p>
      <term>University Faculty Supervisor/Practicum Instructor:</term>
      The University supervisor will be a member of the counseling faculty of Framingham State University. The responsibility of the university supervisor is to meet regularly with both the practicum student and the site supervisor, support the professional activities of the practicum student during the practicum experience; meet with the practicum students in regularly scheduled seminars; and meet with the site supervisor as needed and for a final evaluation of the practicum student. 
    </p>
  </paragraphs>
  <paragraphs>
    <title>Class Activities</title>
    <p>Recorded Role-plays where you will be provided instructor and peer feedback</p>
    <p>Theory to practice conversations using assigned readings and videos</p>
    <p>Case presentations related to your practicum experience (questions/feedback, clinical guidance, ethical issues, reading discussion)</p>
    <p>Reading Discussion and Breakout Activity Groups
  </paragraphs>
  <paragraphs>
  <title>Course and Practicum Objectives</title>
  <subtitle>Objectives Practicum Studens Must Complete
  <p>Demonstrate sensitivity to differences and cultural diversity in the work setting with clients.</p>
  <p>Establish and maintain a client observation/shadow schedule.</p>
  <p>Develop goal setting and treatment planning skills.</p>
  <p>Demonstrate an ability to hear and understand content and effect of client messages.</p>
  <p>Examine agency mission, policies, programs, and surrounding community of the practicum.</p>
  <p>Expand and apply theoretical knowledge appropriate to client population, setting and purpose of the internship setting.</p>
  <p>Demonstrate a commitment to legal, professional, ethical standards, and function within them.</p>
  <p>Consistently exhibit personal and behavioral traits conducive to effective counseling, learning, and professional growth.</p>
  <p>Demonstrate professional behavior at the practicum site, establishing and maintaining effective working relationships with clients, supervisors, and colleagues.</p>
  <p>Demonstrate an understanding of client records, testing and reports that reflects sensitivity and attention to equity and antiracism.</p>
  <p> Maintain a practicum log for documentation of professional activities.</p>
<p> Reflect upon and evaluate interactions with clients, supervisors, and colleagues within the practicum setting.</p>
<p>Develop clinical hypotheses and case formulations.</p>
<subtitle>Assignments, Activities and Evaluations to Meet Objectives
<p>Practicum evaluation, process recordings, course readings, seminar discussions, learning contract, Time2Track reports and activity logs, reflection paper and case presentations</p> 
 </paragraphs>
 <paragraphs>
 <title>Course Requirements/Student Responsibilities</title>
 <ul>Submit the Learning Contract and Affiliation Agreement (signed by student and practicum site supervisor) within one month of the practicum start date. </ul>
<ul>Complete 10-15 min recorded role plays to showcase a portion of a session and your direct interaction with a client (real or scripted) based on the assignment topic of the week. See Canvas for full assignment description. </ul>
<ul>Complete written process recordings for both your site supervisor to review in site supervision sessions and send at least 2 recordings to your faculty supervisor during the semester ensuring site supervisor feedback is present.</ul>   
<ul>Successfully complete 100 clock (site) hours over the semester that must include at minimum the following hours: </ul>
<p>40 hours of direct client contact (face to face or virtual contact only). </p>
<p>10 hours of individual supervision by an approved supervisor. </p>
<p>5 hours of group supervision by an approved supervisor or university supervisor (*1.5hrs of group seminar time is counted each month as part of group sup hours). </p>
<p>10 hours of either additional group or individual supervision or a mix of either. </p>
<ul>Always Maintain ACA and APA Professional Ethics and Standards of Practice. </ul>
<ul>Complete practicum Self-Evaluation, Final Evaluation (with Site Supervisor), in class Case Presentations and practicum Activity Logs via Time2Track app sent monthly to academic supervisor. Full details of assignments are listed on Canvas.</ul>  
<ul>Actively participate in seminar classes with cameras on, in a setting that is professional to prevent distraction (use background filters if needed).</ul>
<ul>Complete assigned seminar readings and actively engage in discussions/round tables, and case consultations.</ul>
<ul>Participate in at least one virtual site visit with your faculty supervisor and field supervisor(s). Notify your site supervisor of date(s) for site visit and provide them with the necessary forms in a timely manner. </ul>
<ul>A portion of your grade for this course will be based on your attendance, active participation in seminars, and your overall engagement and performance in your practicum setting. Consistent attendance, meaningful contributions to discussions, and demonstrating professionalism and growth in your practicum are all key factors in your final evaluation (note: more than two absences per semester will result in a significant lowering of your grade).</ul> 
</subsection>
</section>